%description:

Checks that an MLDv2 host responds to a General Query with a correct Current-State
Report. The IPv6/MLD counterpart of IGMPv3_host2.test (RFC 3810 §6.2; mirrors
RFC 3376 §5.2 for IGMPv3).

A scriptable TestMld tester first joins an SSM group ff3e::1 in INCLUDE mode for one
source, then injects a General Query (multicastAddress unspecified). The host schedules
a delayed response and answers with a MODE_IS_INCLUDE (IS_IN) Current-State Report.
Then the filter is changed to EXCLUDE and another General Query is injected; this time
the host answers with a MODE_IS_EXCLUDE (IS_EX) Current-State Report. Reports are looped
back to the tester and decoded by TestMld::handleMessage.

A small Maximum Response Code (100 ms) is used so that each Query's randomly-delayed
response (uniform(0, maxRespDelay)) fires before the next scenario step. With a large
value, RFC 3810 §6.2 rule 1 (do not schedule a new response while one is pending sooner)
would let the first Query's response slip past the t=3 filter change and report the new
EXCLUDE state instead of the IS_IN expected here.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib
sim-time-limit=300s
cmdenv-express-mode = false

# Fix RNG seed: the host's General-Query response delay is uniform(0, maxRespDelay)
seed-set = 0

#omnetpp 5.0 - 5.1 compatibility:
eventlog-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.elog"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sca"
output-vector-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.vec"
snapshot-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sna"

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TestMLDNetwork
**.mld.typename = "Mldv2"
**.multicastForwarding = false

# RFC 3810 6.1: each State-Change Report is sent [Robustness Variable] (=2) times.
# Shrink the Unsolicited Report Interval so the single retransmission of each change
# fires deterministically (< 1s, before the next step). RNG seed already pinned above.
**.mld.unsolicitedReportInterval = 0.5s

**.scenarioManager.script = xmldoc("scenario.xml")

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

%file: scenario.xml
<scenario>

<join t="2" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" group="ff3e::1" sources="2001::1"/>
<dump t="2" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" what="groups"/>
<send t="2" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" type="Mldv2Query" maxRespCode="100"/>

<set-filter t="3" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" group="ff3e::1" sources="E 2001::2"/>
<dump t="3" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" what="groups"/>
<send t="3" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" type="Mldv2Query" maxRespCode="100"/>

</scenario>

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

%#
%# First check that the join/set-filter were applied to the interface state
%#
%postrun-command: grep "TestMld: .*groups =" test.out > groups.out || true
%contains: groups.out
TestMld: eth0: groups = ff3e::1 I 2001::1.
TestMld: eth0: groups = ff3e::1 E 2001::2.

%#
%# Now check that the Mldv2 module responded to each General Query with a Current-State
%# Report. The join at t=2 (INCLUDE()->INCLUDE(2001::1)) and the t=3 filter change
%# (INCLUDE->EXCLUDE) are State-Change Reports, so each is sent twice (RFC 3810 6.1,
%# [Robustness Variable] = 2): the immediate ALLOW/TO_EX plus one retransmission,
%# interleaved with the IS_IN/IS_EX Current-State responses to the General Queries.
%#
%postrun-command: grep "TestMld: .*Received" test.out > received.out || true
%contains-regex: received.out
TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=ALLOW \(2001::1\)>.
(?:.*\n)*?TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=IS_IN \(2001::1\)>.
(?:.*\n)*?TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=ALLOW \(2001::1\)>.
(?:.*\n)*?TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=TO_EX \(2001::2\)>.
(?:.*\n)*?TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=IS_EX \(2001::2\)>.
(?:.*\n)*?TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=TO_EX \(2001::2\)>.

%#
%# Explicitly assert the State-Change Report retransmission (RFC 3810 6.1).
%#
%postrun-command: grep "Retransmitting State-Change Report" test.out > retransmit.out || true
%contains: retransmit.out
Retransmitting State-Change Report for group 'ff3e::1' on interface 'eth0' (1 transmission(s) left).
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
